\f0\b\fs66 \cf0 Arborio Rice Pudding\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\fs40 \cf2 Yield:  \cf0 6 to 8 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa240\ql\qnatural

\fs52 \cf0 INGREDIENTS\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl260\sa280\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2 quarts milk\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons butter\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cups sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon, plus more for dusting\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 vanilla bean, split and seeds scraped\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl260\sa280\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 cup Arborio rice\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1/2 cups water\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 orange, zested, 1 teaspoon plus more for garnish\
{\listtext	\'95	}Pinch kosher salt\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b\fs52 \cf0 DIRECTIONS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa160\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs48 \cf3 Take a large saucepan and add milk, butter, sugar, cinnamon, and vanilla bean and seeds. Cook the rice in boiling water until al dente. Once the water has evaporated fold in milk mixture. Reduce heat to medium and cook for 10 minutes stirring regularly until rice is tender. Add the orange zest and pinch of salt. Stir well and remove from heat. The consistency should be more liquid than regular risotto. Finish with a light dust of cinnamon.\
